Year: 1964 (5), 1972 (2-3), 1975 (4,6), 1977 (1)
Label: Verve (Digitally Remastered, 1988)

I believe this album is one of Stan's most profound projects.  Discontinued by the production company, this album still influences my playing to this day!  For instance, the one thing that drew me to this song was how he opened Willow Weep For Me as he "weeps" for attention in an introducing cadenza. ~ Jeffrey C. Sandberg, Amazon.com
